<section id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Straight answers.</h2>
    <div style="margin-top:36px;max-width:820px">
      <details><summary>Are you attorneys?</summary><div class="a">Writ Large's writing team consists of accredited paralegals with experience in the federal system, not attorneys. If your situation looks like it needs full attorney representation rather than document preparation, we'll tell you — see how our <a href="/litigation/">litigation support works</a>.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Do you guarantee results?</summary><div class="a">No, and nobody in this line of work should. Courts decide outcomes, not us. What we can promise is a properly researched, properly formatted motion that gives your case the best chance it has.</div></details>
      <details><summary>How long does a motion take to prepare?</summary><div class="a">Turnaround varies by document and current volume — we'll give you a specific timeline before you commit to anything. Court decisions themselves can take considerably longer than our preparation time.</div></details>
      <details><summary>How do I get the finished document?</summary><div class="a">Completed documents are mailed directly to your facility. You review the draft before anything is finalized.</div></details>
      <details><summary>What if I'm not sure which motion I need?</summary><div class="a">Tell us your situation — facility, sentence, and what's changed. We'll tell you honestly which motion, if any, fits, before you pay for anything.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Is this connected to Prisoner Legal Aid?</summary><div class="a">Yes — Writ Large is a Prisoner Legal Aid resource, focused specifically on federal post-conviction document preparation. For civil rights litigation and full attorney representation, see how our <a href="/litigation/">litigation support works</a>.</div></details>
